channel.title: My item transfer method
channel.description:
The safest way that I have thought of to transfer autoed items, is to log on proxy'ed Aryan, then log on RS with your mule normally with your regular IP.
Then either trade or drop trade your items, so that if they track it, it shows as 2 different IP's.
Is there any better way to transfer?

item.title: My item transfer method
item.dc:creator: @muerte4 muerte4
item.description:
@muerte4 wrote:

someone suggested this to me and it’s pretty good.

Ok you have 10 bots, trade all the bots with each other until one bot has everything. Next enter your main from firefox behind your genuine ip, enter ur bot through aryan behind a proxy… enter the same world as your bot, next make your bot attack something it can’t kill (make sure to give it no armor or weapons XD) like a unicorn (my bots are usually lvl 10 max) once it dies run in and collect your loot. So far this has worked for me, all credit goes to whoever suggested it to me… can’t remember name. Make sure to make it fight something not too close to people so that someone else doesn’t run in and steal your loot.

item.title: My item transfer method
item.dc:creator: @MujaheD Radeon
item.description:
@MujaheD wrote:

[quote=“intheknow, post:17, topic:1810”]What about this guys:

Using a proxy for your auto, log on and climb a ladder to a remote location that has a table. Then, “use gold with the table”.

Next:

Log on from your home IP and snatch the gold when it appears.

The main advantage of this is there is no way to prove the transfer was intended for your main. The gold, after all, showed up on the screen visible to everyone (such as the busy range in catherby). Sure it looks suspicious placing 1m on a table… but that means your autoer is toast, not your main.

item.description:

[quote=“LIMiTER, post:13, topic:1810”]I have find this way simple:

-use my own ip for the mainers(they can’t ban the mainers before mining lvl 60;))
-drop ores and pick with the mule
-after every picking I change my proxy (with IE it’s very easy, good proxy site http://www.proxy4free.com/page1.html )
-they can’t track me (using this method, they haven’t banned any mules from me.)

and if you make a mistake, you can always install also firefox or opera and use there also other ip’s and then drop the stuff with IE to other mule using firefox/opera

the only mistake is to use same ip’s, it is good to change proxy as often as possible. also changing mules after week or two is a good, securing way to keep your golds…[/quote]

only 1 problem ;p jagex sees trough IE proxy’s… you have to set a proxy in the runbot.bat (a socks5)
